title: For Sale:   Colts Patents Arms Manufacturing Company -- Gun and Display from the William Ruger Collection
postcontent: This gun is from the William Ruger Collection and was purchased from his grandson. It is reported to have belonged to Frank Tenney Johnson, a famous Western artist active at the same time as Russell and Remington. The .41 Colt, the holster and gun belt, and the display case are all from the Ruger Collection. Also included, is a framed authenticated print of a 1936 Frank Tenney Johnson painting, "On the Range", which was added at a later date. The gun is in excellent mechanical condition and fine cosmetic condition. Case hardening remains on the hammer and frame and the original blue has thinned except on the barrel next to the frame. All serial numbers match, except the loading gate which, as is normal, has an assembly number, and the grips fit well, but are worn. The holster has a tear at the muzzle end, probably from being drawn repeatedly. There are some "dings" on the barrel just forward of the ".41 Colt", and I have no idea what may have caused them. It is apparent that Tenney did not leave this weapon in a closet. This weapon would be an outstanding acquisition for a collector who can display it properly. I cannot, and hence, am selling it to someone who can showcase it as it deserves. The gun was manufactured in 1899 and an FFL is required for shipment. you can contact me via seccoalis@gmail.com, selling this to get some money, its worth more than 2850 , my loss is your gain

title: For Sale:  TO THE PRICE GOUGERS AND PEOPLE WHO MAY BE NEW TO SHOOTING
location: NORTH CAROLINA, North Carolina, United States
postcontent:
Dear price gougers, if you want to make 20 or 30% and take advantage of people who don't shoot much, go ahead.  Most of us who shoot every weekend, and have for most of our lives have been through this before, 2008, 1994, etc.  But trying to make a 100% on stuff just makes us mad.  This isn't drug dealing, you can still get this stuff.   Here is a small list for you people that may have not realized what prices were.
9mm blazer ammo should never be more than 13.00 a box
9mm american eagle should never be more than 15.00 a box
if you put 9mm on here for nearly $1 a round as I have seen, think about what you are doing.
Kel tec pistols are never more than $299 new.  They are on the shelves right now in the triad area,  don't email me and ask, go look.
7.62X39 ammo is all over right now for $8.95 a box, again  if you are putting this on here for $15 a box have fun.
You are forcing prices up unnecessarilly.  We don't mind if you make a little off of people who have jobs and don't have time to scavenge at wal mart like buzzards, but listing these riduculous prices for .22 ammo makes people think thats ok.  Again for those of you who don't know.... at the worst a box of 525 rounds of .22 LR ammo costs $23.99.  If you gougers want to sell it for $30 go ahead but to list that for $50 just looks stupid.  I might as well ask for a piece of land for a case of ammo.
I think the AR craze is almost over, but for those of you who don't know, prior to the events of the last few months, you could go to wal mart and buy a DPMS .308 AR rifle for $972 out the door,  You could buy one in .223 for about $800 out the door, and there were even ones with less features in the $675 area.  Most big time gun stores have AR rifles back in stock.  To the price gougers.... again, we don't mind if you make $100 on a rifle, but $300.  When this is all over, those of us who enjoy shooting every weekend will still be here, while you gougers are gone.  If you are among the shooters, keep flagging these idiots posts until they leave or at least come down to a price that's not an insult to our intelligence.   And one more thing, if you have time to sit at the Wal Marts before they open, would you please take 5 extra minutes and write or call your elected officials and ask them not to vote for any new gun control measures.  Thanks.
